      • emitIntegerExponentiation

        public void emitIntegerExponentiation()
        Emits an Integer Exponentiation, which consumes the two upmost Elements of the Stack. The upmost is interpreted as the power, the one below as base. The result is than pushed onto the Stack. The consumed Elements are interpreted as Integer Numbers.
